  "system": {
    "description": {
      "type": "String",
      "label": "Description",
      "value": "<p>You send a single crackling arc of green energy at the target. Crackling Doom is a <em>magic missile</em> with a Damage of +4. In addition, anyone damaged by this spell must make a successful <strong>Challenging (+0) Endurance</strong> Test or gain one @Condition[Stunned] Condition for every SL on the Casting Test.</p><p>\n\n <b>Lore:</b> <p>The Lore of Ruin channels the terrible power of Warpstone to lash out at targets, often incinerating them whole. It is focused on destruction and disintegration, and is feared throughout Skavendom and beyond.</p>  <p>This terrible power is highly invigorating and the sensation of barely restrained energy is almost addictive. Whenever you successfully cast a spell from the Lore of Ruin, you may add +1 SL to any Initiative- or Agility-based Tests for the next [[/br 1d10]] rounds.</p>  <p>Ingredients: Grey Seers use various scraps of fur, hide, bones, and crystalline Warpstone when casting spells from the Lore of Ruin.</p><p>"
    },
